headline: Compared to Estimates, Rollins (ROL) Q3 Earnings: A Look at Key Metrics
summary: While the top- and bottom-line numbers for Rollins (ROL) give a sense of how the business performed in the quarter ended September 2025, it could be worth looking at how some of its key metrics compare to Wall Street estimates and year-ago values.

headline: ROL Q3 Deep Dive: M&A Integration and Commercial Investments Propel Growth Amid Stable Margins
summary: Pest control company Rollins (NYSE:ROL) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 12% year on year to $1.03 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.35 per share was 6.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Does Rollins’ (ROL) Dividend Hike Reflect Stronger Fundamentals or a Shift in Capital Priorities?
summary: Rollins, Inc. announced in late October that its Board of Directors approved an 11% increase to its regular quarterly cash dividend, setting the new amount at US$0.1825 per share for payment on December 10, 2025, to shareholders of record as of November 10, 2025. This marks more than an 80% total increase in the company's regular quarterly dividend since early 2022, highlighting ongoing capital returns and management's confidence in the business outlook.
